(35, 'Study in UK', 'study-in-uk', 'UK', 'Main', 'Normal', 5, NULL, '<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Study in United Kingdom (UK) </strong></span><br />\r\nEngland, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland are parts of United Kingdom (UK) also known as Britain. UK has fairest legal system in the world with democratic norms and value. British people are one of the most highly developed civilization and culture after Japan. It has lots of monuments and attractions such as Tower of London, Buckingham Palace, Tower Bridge (also known as London Bridge). Nepalese are most respectful people among the people from different continents or sub-continents in Britain because of British Gurkha Regimen. For Nepalese student, UK is not far in the sense they won’t feel homesick because lots of Nepalese are there in UK and even you can have food of your taste as in your home.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUK has world’s top universities like Cambridge University, Oxford University, King’s College London. Post Brexit time shows potential of immigrants and higher potential job market since massive flow of EU citizens to UK is now bottlenecked.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Why UK as study Destination </strong></span><br />\r\n<strong>1. Top ranked universities and educational system</strong><br />\r\nUK University or college degree is highly recognized in the world because of its high quality of teaching methodology and updated to current world technologies and methodologies. Universities and colleges have faculties with focused curricular activities sharpening their students’ skills and to make well prepared to world job market. Because of its high-quality educational system, UK has 4 Universities within top 10 Universities according to QS University rankings.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>2. World- leading Research </strong><br />\r\nUniversities in UK are research based and UK ranks third in innovation in the world recognized by Research Assessment Exercise (RAE) as ‘world-leading’ and ‘internationally excellent’. RAE is the body to monitor and assess the quality standards for research activities of colleges and universities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>3. Highly advanced teaching methodology</strong><br />\r\nUniversities in UK provide students to learn independently and sharpen the analytical power of individuals which is reflected as star rating teaching methodology. UK Universities has advanced teaching methodologies and uses the advanced tools and techniques for learning practice.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>4. Wide varieties of course offers</strong><br />\r\nUK has Universities and colleges focusing both on theoretical and professional learning. Some of the universities and colleges are highly concentrated on professional skill development such as computing, accounting and marketing while some of universities are highly focused on theory and researches. UK universities are well recognized for both business studies like MBA or business administrations and technological study like computing, telecommunication, power studies; additionally, Universities and colleges has diverse course of study options.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>5. Lower educational cost </strong><br />\r\nOne of the important points to speak in high volume is lower cost of education for international students. US educations cost $30,000 in average while UK education costs £6,000 to £12,000 (equivalently $8,000 to $16,000 at most). Moreover UK degree has less time duration for completion compared to USA education system since UK has 3 terms (4 months each) in a year while USA has 2 terms (6 months each) in a year.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>6. Numerous scholarships and work opportunities </strong><br />\r\nUK universities and government have numerous scholarships and grants for international students. Over 20,000 international students get financial aid from UK government. Additionally, students can work when they are studying – up to 20 hours per week during study period and more in terms holidays.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>7. Life experience and cultural exploration </strong><br />\r\nStudying abroad is not only the equipping you with skills and knowledge but also exploring the cultures and lifestyle of the country you are studying. UK has worlds’ best transportation system in regards to public bus and train as transportation lines. Additionally, it has direct train lines to European Countries through sea-water – amazing technologies and development.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Top courses that UK Universities offers</strong></span>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Accounting and finance</li>\r\n	<li>Aeronautical &amp; manufacturing Engineering</li>\r\n	<li>Architecture</li>\r\n	<li>Computer Science</li>\r\n	<li>Economics</li>\r\n	<li>Marketing</li>\r\n	<li>Food and beverage</li>\r\n	<li>Hospitality, Leisure, and Tourism</li>\r\n	<li>Electrical and Electronics Engineering &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Undergraduate Courses in UK </strong><br />\r\nAll the applicants to UK universities are required to apply through Universities and Colleges Admission Service (UCAS) – a centralized body for admission and placements. Once you are accepted from UCAS, you are eligible to apply 5 different courses in UCAS recognized universities or colleges with flexibility of 5 different courses to a university or 5 different universities for a courses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Masters in UK </strong><br />\r\nUnlike undergraduate study, masters’ degree has not centralized application system as UCAS for undergraduate applications. UK universities has multiple of entry time in a year depending up on universities. Generally, international students have application deadline earlier than home students of EU students.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', 4, '1548224720_uk.jpg', NULL, '1549273998_uk-banner.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Study in UK', NULL, '1', '2019-01-21 04:30:13', '2019-02-04 15:53:18'),
(36, 'Study in Ireland', 'study-in-ireland', 'Ireland', 'Main', 'Normal', 6, NULL, '<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Ireland as a Study Destination</strong></span><br />\r\nIreland is rich in culture with traditions deep-rooted historically. Ireland provides one of the top educations in Europe. It is famous as the land of leprechauns, castles, warriors, elves, and balladeers. Higher education in Ireland includes university education, colleges and instituted to provide wide range of education. Institutions in Ireland cover wide range of vocational programmes in hospitality, healthcare, media, textiles, etc. statistics shows that international student in Ireland is increasing every year. Cultures in Ireland are one of the highly developed and civilized; so, warmest people in the world.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nFollowing are the reasons to select Ireland as your next land for higher education which could contribute in your career path; and these justifies Ireland as your choice of study destination.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>1. World-class universities in Ireland </strong><br />\r\nIreland has world’s top universities recognized all over the world. Ireland education system focuses on heuristic methodology of education. Huge amount of investment in education and research makes the universities in Ireland world-ranked. Ireland has educational quality and links parallel to UK and USA universities.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>2. High quality research </strong><br />\r\nIreland has thousands of dollar investment annually in research in their higher education; which ultimately grows their universities as top research universities in the field of natural science, social science and humanities in the world.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>3. Great opportunities for industrial exposure and Post Study Work</strong><br />\r\nUndergraduate or higher level of study students in Ireland has work opportunity during study period up to 20 hours per week while more than 20 hours in holidays. High skilled English speaking manpower are highly demanding in Ireland and so student has great opportunities to tie up industries at both study and post study time. After completion of Bachelor’s degree study or above, student could have Post-Study work permit; under which student may remain in Ireland after their study. In Post Study work, a student can stay and work full time up to 24 months.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>4. Home to world’s leading companies</strong><br />\r\nIreland is second hub for world’s leading companies after Singapore. Ireland has 9 out of 10 EU pharmaceuticals operating as main office; which implies greater opportunities for job after your college or university education.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>5. Affordable education and accommodation </strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\nUniversities and colleges in Ireland have lesser tuition fee and cost of living compared to US and UK study stay. Another financial benefit is shorter period of stay that is most degree programme has one year long which reduces the living cost.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>6. Friendly and safe for international students </strong><br />\r\nAs quoted by Lonely Planet, Ireland is the friendliest country in the world. Ireland people are world renowned friendly. People in Ireland are highly civilized in terms of culture.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>7. Plenty of scholarship </strong><br />\r\nIreland governments and educational institutions – universities and colleges – in Ireland have various scholarships for international students depending upon your study of subjects. Majority of the programmes offer scholarship and funding opportunities to their students. &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Education in Ireland</strong></span><br />\r\nThere are four types of educational certification in Ireland.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Non-University Level</strong>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Two-years of certification</li>\r\n	<li>Three-years of Diploma</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>University Level </strong>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Bachelors Degree</li>\r\n	<li>Bachelor’s Degree (Honours)</li>\r\n	<li>Higher Diploma</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Master’s degree</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Post-graduate Diploma</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Top universities in Ireland</strong><br />\r\nIreland has top universities in the field of study chemistry and Nanotechnology, agriculture science and mathematics. Students could have broad range of courses over 5’000 programmes recognized internationally.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Top universities in Ireland </strong>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Trinity College Dublin and University of Dublin</li>\r\n	<li>University College Cork</li>\r\n	<li>University College Dublin</li>\r\n	<li>Dublin City University</li>\r\n	<li>University of Limerick</li>\r\n	<li>National University of Ireland, Galway</li>\r\n	<li>Dublin Institute of Technology</li>\r\n	<li>National University of Ireland, Maynooth</li>\r\n	<li>Royal College of Surgeons in Ireland</li>\r\n	<li>Cork Institute of Technology</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Study in Ireland: When and How to Apply </strong><br />\r\nIreland has centralized admission process for all the universities and colleges named Central Application Office (CAO). But for post-graduate courses, students directly apply to the chosen universities. Followings are some of the popular courses in Universities or colleges in Ireland:\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Arts and literature</li>\r\n	<li>Information technology</li>\r\n	<li>Management</li>\r\n	<li>History</li>\r\n	<li>Engineering</li>\r\n	<li>Biotechnology and Pharmacy</li>\r\n	<li>Applied Science and Hospitality</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>English requirements</strong>:<br />\r\nMost universities in Ireland need IELTS score of 6.5 or higher for UG and above. Universities can also accept PTE Academic score of 51-58 for UG and 59-64 for Post graduate (PG); while TOEFL iBT of minimum of 90.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Eligibility for undergraduate </strong>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Majority of university require 12 years of secondary education, your academic credentials are most important though.</li>\r\n	<li>Minimal aggregate of 65% or above in 12<sup>th</sup> grade is required.</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum IELTS band score as requested by your University</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Eligibility for Post Graduate&nbsp; </strong>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>For Master’s study, Ireland universities requires Bachelor’s equivalent which is 16 years of formal education.</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum IELTS/PTE Academic scores</li>\r\n	<li>Relevant work experience in case of MBA programme.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Visa requirements for International Students</strong><br />\r\nOnce you have decision that you will study in Ireland, you should get student visa to enter and study in Ireland. For the visa grant, one should complete the following requirements:\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Acceptance letter from Irish educational institution with confirmation of your enrollment as full time student</li>\r\n	<li>Duly completed and signed application form, with two passport-size photographs.</li>\r\n	<li>You will have to pay non refundable visa application fee</li>\r\n	<li>Evidence of scholarship if any</li>\r\n	<li>Evidence of sufficient fund to support study and living for one year which is € 7,000.</li>\r\n	<li>Official English language test score as required by your institution&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>A private medical insurance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', 4, '1548224732_ireland.jpg', NULL, '1549274743_Dublin-1400x500.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Study in Ireland', NULL, '1', '2019-01-21 04:30:30', '2019-02-04 16:05:43'),
(37, 'Study in Germany', 'study-in-germany', 'Germany', 'Main', 'Normal', 7, NULL, '<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Study Destination Germany&nbsp;</strong></span><br />\r\nGermany is pioneer in technological innovation and scientific explore with high quality products and educations. Being industrial hub for world, it has high employment prospects. It is 3<sup>rd</sup> most popular study destination among the international students over the world and obviously quality education at no cost. More than 3,00,000 international students are studying in Germany with unique blend of cultures, high standard living.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Why Germany as Educational Destination </strong></span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>1. High Quality Education for no Cost at all </strong><br />\r\nOutstandingly, one can think “there is no such thing as a free lunch” but German education system has. So, public universities in Germany offer high quality education for free not only for domestic students but also for international students. German education is highly qualitative and widely accepted across the world. German Universities are highly research based. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>2. World’s Fourth Largest Economy </strong><br />\r\nGerman is the largest economy in European Union (EU) and forth largest in the world after USA, China and Japan. Innovations and global networking are keys to lead the Germany to this position of Global economy.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>3. Numerous Scholarship Programmes</strong><br />\r\nGerman government offers numbers scholarship programmes and financial aid which could assist students’ accommodation. This is because the German government believes international students are supposed to contribute in knowledge during the university study.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>4. Excellent Employment Prospects as Global industrial Hub</strong><br />\r\nForeign students are allowed to work in Germeny at institutes, library or other facilities in the campus under employment law; for violation of employment laws, student could be debarred to respective country. Studying in Germany has excellent career prospects as universities and institutions have a partnership with multinational companies. Most multinational companies have presence in the country – creating limitless career opportunities after the completion of studies. &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>5. A Safe and Welcoming Environment</strong><br />\r\nAmicable and highly disciplined people in Germany make lower crime rate and safest countries in the world. In addition to that, the country has best support service to the international students.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>6. Easy of Visa Acquisition and Residency </strong><br />\r\nThe government of German has large investment in both quality of education and infrastructure to attract international students – eventually highest percentage of investment to make free education. International students are permitted to stay in Germany for a period of 18 months once they completed the study – during the period they are eligible for full time job.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>7. World’s biggest country for Engineering and Research based Programmes </strong><br />\r\nGermany universities are known for its high quality engineering degree with diverse courses – more than 3500 engineering courses and<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Eligibility Criteria</strong><br />\r\nDifferent German University has different admission requirements depending up on their own courses and programmes. Certain universities in Germany require German language skill as admission requirements; however, knowledge of German language is beneficent for easy living. When universities ask for German language skill test, students are required to take DSH, TestDaF or GDS to submit as proficiency certificate.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>English Language Proficiency </strong><br />\r\nAll international applicants are required to take recognized IELTS/TOEFL as English proficiency test. In case of IELTS test, 6.5 band score is required, and for TOEFL score more than 80 is required.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Undergraduate requirements</strong>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>High school education or 13 years of education is essential.</li>\r\n	<li>Good academic record in +2 level.</li>\r\n	<li>Some of the universities may ask for SAT scores.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Post-graduate requirement </strong>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Recognized undergraduate degree or 16 years of education is required to enroll in post graduate level, while some of the universities accept 3 years bachelors or undergraduate degree.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong academic background in most recent programmes.</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum of 2 years work experience might required for MBA programme in certain Universities.</li>\r\n	<li>Though GRE/GMAT is optional some of the universities recommend for the tests.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Document Checklist for Different Level of Study</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Bachelors in Germany: </strong>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Notarized copies of class 10<sup>th</sup> and 12<sup>th</sup> mark sheet, and certificates.</li>\r\n	<li>IELTS (notarized) or TOEFL score</li>\r\n	<li>Notarized copy of Passport.</li>\r\n	<li>One letter of recommendation from previous school.</li>\r\n	<li>Statement of purpose (SOP).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Masters in Germany:</strong>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Notarized copy mark-sheets all previous schools.</li>\r\n	<li>Official transcripts</li>\r\n	<li>Application form and application Fee.</li>\r\n	<li>IELTS (notarized) or TOEFL scores.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>GRE or GMAT scores if university requires.</li>\r\n	<li>Two letter of recommendation from university or college</li>\r\n	<li>Work experience (if any)</li>\r\n	<li>Statement of purpose (SOP)</li>\r\n	<li>Notarized copy of passport</li>\r\n	<li>Extracurricular activities certificates.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>List of top Universities according QS rankings (2019)</strong>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Technical University of Munich (#61)</li>\r\n	<li>Ludwig-Maximulians- Universitat (#62)</li>\r\n	<li>Ruprecht-Karls-Universitat (#64)</li>\r\n	<li>KIT, Karlsruhe Institute of Telecommunication (#116)</li>\r\n	<li>Humboldt – Universitat Zu Berlin (#121)</li>\r\n	<li>Freie Universitaet Berlin (#130)</li>\r\n	<li>RWTH Aachen University (#144)</li>\r\n	<li>Technische Universitat Berlin (#147)</li>\r\n	<li>Eberhard Karls Universitat Tub (#168)</li>\r\n	<li>Albert-Ludwigs-Universitaet Fr (#186)</li>\r\n	<li>Technische Universitat Dresden (#191)</li>\r\n</ol>', 4, '1548224749_german.jpg', NULL, '1549274958_banner-dresden2.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Study in Germany', NULL, '1', '2019-01-21 04:30:47', '2019-02-13 11:33:12'),
(38, 'Study in India', 'study-in-india', 'India', 'Main', 'Normal', 8, NULL, '<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Study Destination India&nbsp;</strong></span><br />\r\nIn recent decade, Indian Universities and Colleges are one of the study destinations for thousands of students for lower cost of education and living cost. Fastest growing economy and growing universities in India is one of the most attractive things to Nepalese students to turn their dream into true. MBBS, Nursing and Engineering programmes in Indian Universities or Colleges are fascinating subjects of study for Nepalese students.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Why India as study Destination </strong></span><br />\r\n<strong>1. Lots of scholarship for Nepalese students from Indian Government</strong><br />\r\nAlong with closest diplomatic and geographic relation to India, thousands of Nepalese students are awarded hundreds of different scholarships to support study in Indian Universities and Colleges. Each year, thousands of Nepalese students are awarded by Indian government through Indian Embassy Nepal. So, thousands of Nepalese students are most welcome in Indian Universities in different states of India.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>2. Diverse course choices </strong><br />\r\nHundreds of Universities and colleges in India are offering programmes as offered around the globe to product skilled manpower to global market. India universities and colleges have diverse course options big universities such as IIT, MIT, NIT in different states of India. Nepalese students are fascinated to medical science such as MBBS, Nursing and Pharmacy programmes and Engineering programmes such as Electrical, Civil, Mechanical, Electronics and Communication Engineering in Indian Universities and colleges.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>3. Lots of multinational companies </strong><br />\r\nWith the establishment of different multinational companies such as IBM, Google, Qualcomm, Micro-Soft in different city of India, there is huge consumption of technical persons such as computer engineering, electronics engineering or electrical engineering. So, for a student studying in different engineering subjects in Indian Universities and colleges is one of the opportunities to explore their potential and making career in multinational companies. &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>4. Placement facilities </strong><br />\r\nWith the presence of multinational companies in different cities of India, there is growth of placement opportunities for students in Universities or colleges. So, most of the technical students in Indian institutes get placement to IBM, Google, Qualcomm etc. even from 6<sup>th</sup> or 7<sup>th</sup> semester and starts their career in multinational companies.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>5. Fastest growing world economy</strong><br />\r\nBeing India is fastest growing economy in the world; it consumes large numbers of skilled manpower in medical science, computer science or other engineering fields. So, both undergraduate and graduate student has huge opportunities in India to start dream career.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>6. Massive growth in research activities </strong><br />\r\nStudents must have knowledge of how much research activities are conducting in the field of subject they want to enroll. They must understand that higher the research activities higher the opportunities grow their career in that particular subject area. Since Indian government and agencies are investing larger amount to research, there is higher chance of career growth.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>7. Shared cultural and life style</strong><br />\r\nIndia and Nepal not only shares boarder pillars but also cultures and life style. Because of these shared cultural values and lifestyle, Nepalese students could have easy life in India. Moreover, because of especial diplomatic relation between Nepal and India, travel is easier compared to other countries.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Some top ranked Universities in India by QS University Rankings (2019)</strong>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Indian Institute of Technology (#162)</li>\r\n	<li>Indian Institute of Science (#170)</li>\r\n	<li>Indian Institute of Technology (#172)</li>\r\n	<li>Indian Institute of Technology (#264)</li>\r\n	<li>Indian Institute of Technology (#283)</li>\r\n	<li>Indian Institute of Technology (#295)</li>\r\n	<li>University of Delhi (#487)</li>\r\n	<li>University of Mumbai</li>\r\n	<li>University of Calcutta</li>\r\n	<li>Vellore Institute of Technology</li>\r\n</ol>', 4, '1548224766_india.jpg', NULL, '1549279730_bangalore-preset3.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Study in India', NULL, '1', '2019-01-21 04:31:09', '2019-02-04 17:28:50'),
(39, 'Study in South Korea', 'study-in-south-korea', 'South Korea', 'Main', 'Normal', 9, NULL, '<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>Study in South Korea</strong></span><br />\r\nEducation is highly competitive and lower cost education in comparison to that English speaking country. Korea is ranked 1<sup>st</sup> in the study of information and communication technology by international telecommunication union (ITU). Additionally, Recently, Korean government has increased the number of scholarship to foreign student. For international students, classes are English medium and Korean language courses are also available.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWithin last 5 years number of international graduate student in Korean university has been risen up drastically. According to April 2016, as indicated by the government of Korea, roughly 104,000 international students are studying in Korea, among which 63,000 students are in the graduate programme; and for international students, 30% of the courses in Korea is taught in English medium as instructors’ language. Korea is safe and comfortable resident with great weather and nature and high standard of living.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nGenerally, Korean University has two intakes namely fall – run May to June and spring – runs between September to November. Korean colleges accept 2-3 years of study after higher secondary or +2 equivalent while 4-6 years of undergraduate course in Universities. Master’s level of study is 2 years of study, and while PhD is at least 2 years course. Korean government provides two types of study visa for international students; D-2 is required by the international student to study regular courses in Korean institute while D-4 visa is required to study Korean language courses in Korean universities. One who wants to study in Korea has to apply for a certificate of visa issuance approval to competent immigration office; once is used by the Korean consulate to issue Korean visa.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Education system in South Korea</strong><br />\r\nThe Korean education is a single-track system, with 6 years of elementary school, 3 years of middle school and 3 years of high school which equivalent +2 in Nepal. After 3 years of high school education, students are eligible to study in 4 years undergraduate university education.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Some top Universities (QS World University Rankings - 2019) </strong>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\r\n	<li>Seoul National University (#36)</li>\r\n	<li>Korea Advanced Institute of Science &amp; Technology (KAIST) (#40)</li>\r\n	<li>Pohang University of Science and Technology (POSTECH) (#83)</li>\r\n	<li>Korea University (#86)</li>\r\n	<li>Sungkyunkwan University (#100)</li>\r\n	<li>Yonsei University (#107)</li>\r\n	<li>Hanyang University (#151)</li>\r\n	<li>Kyung Hee University (#264)</li>\r\n	<li>Gwangju Institute of Science and Technology (#339)</li>\r\n	<li>Chung-Ang University (#397)</li>\r\n</ol>', 4, '1548585549_south-korea.jpg', NULL, '1549276187_SK-Banner.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Study in South Korea', NULL, '1', '2019-01-21 04:31:27', '2019-02-04 16:29:47'),
